{
  "texts": [
    "Negative-valued pixels in THEMIS images are replaced with zeros in line with the previous Sgr A * analysis (Sgr A * 2017 III; Sgr A * 2017 IV).",
    "We use two image domain feature extraction tools, REx and VIDA.",
    "The Ring Extractor (REx) is available as part of eht-imaging and is described in detail in M 87 * 2017 IV.",
    "The second IDFE tool, Variational Image-Domain Analysis (VIDA, Tiede et al. 2022a), uses parameterized templates to approximate an image and adjusts the parameter values until a specified cost function, in the form of a probability divergence that provides a distance metric between the image and template, is minimized.",
    "We use an updated version of the SymCosineRingwFloor template used in Sgr A * 2017 IV to match the mF-ring model described later in Sect. 6.2."
  ]
}